				<h2>Clinical</h2>
				<p>
				The Greehey Children’s Cancer Research Institute (Greehey CCRI) collaborates closely with the <a>Division of Pediatric Hematology-Oncology at UT Health San Antonio</a> to support clinical research initiatives. This includes the collection and annotation of clinical specimens to advance patient-centered research. As part of our mission to conduct research that directly informs clinical care, Greehey CCRI provides the essential infrastructure for human subjects’ research and investigator-initiated trials in pediatric cancer. Given the collaborative nature of pediatric cancer research, Greehey CCRI also facilitates the involvement of investigators in national cooperative group trials, such as those led by the Children’s Oncology Group.</p>

<p><a>UT Health San Antonio MD Anderson Cancer Center</a> is also a member of The Pediatric Oncology Experimental Therapeutics Investigators’ Consortium (POETIC). POETIC studies in pediatric oncology focus on the biological underpinnings of anti-cancer therapies and the early-phase development of new agents and innovative therapeutic combinations.
				</p>

				<h2>Education</h2>
				<p>
					The Greehey Children’s Cancer Research Institute is dedicated to training the next generation of pediatric cancer researchers. Our educational mission focuses on developing a robust pipeline of talent, offering opportunities for undergraduates through summer research programs, medical students in the MD with Distinction in Research program, fellows in the ACGME-accredited hematology-oncology fellowship, and graduate students in Cancer Biology and related fields. We also provide a supportive environment for post-doctoral research training. Over the past five years, we have graduated over a dozen PhDs, trained four pediatric oncology fellows, and hosted numerous undergraduate students for summer research.
				</p>
